gomodel:SYNGO_1046  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Mossy fiber posttetanic potentiation (PTP) and LTP measured in CA3 granule neurons after tetanic stimulation induced in the stratum lucidum is impaired in hetero- and homozygotic ephrin-B3lacZ mice that express a mutant, likely dominant-negative (Fig. 4), version of ephrin-B3 (β-galactosidase fused to intracellular C-terminus of ephrin-B3) (Fig 3). Short-term plasticity in the mossy fibers in these mice was normal (Fig. 5). Experimental description: Hippocampal tissue was dissected from postnatal day 1 (PD1) mice" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1046" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

